33 A.3d 479 ATTORNEY GRIEVANCE COMMISSION OF MARYLAND, Petitioner v. Anthony J. DELAURENTIS, Respondent. Misc. Docket AG No. 49,

Sept. Term, 2011.

Court of Appeals of Maryland. Dec. 15, 2011.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the Joint Petition for Disbarment By Consent filed herein pursuant to Maryland Rule 16-772, it is this 15th day of December, 2011,

ORDERED, by the Court of Appeals of Maryland, that Anthony J. DeLaurentis be, and he hereby is, disbarred by consent from the practice of law in the State of Maryland, effective immediately; and it is further

ORDERED, that the Clerk of this Court, shall strike the name of Anthony J. DeLaurentis from the register of attorneys in this Court and, pursuant to Maryland Rule 16 — 772(d), shall certify to the Trustees of the Client Protection Fund of the Bar of Maryland and the clerks of all judicial tribunals in the State that the name of Anthony J. DeLaurentis has been so stricken.
